                <head>208. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>During the years 1955–1957, the “special relationship” between the United States
                    and the United Kingdom underwent its most severe trial. That trial, following
                    the nationalization of the Suez Canal Company in July 1956, is fully documented
                    in volume XVI. The documents printed here concentrate on Anglo-American
                    bilateral relations. The documents reflect the “special relationship,”
                    particularly in the extensive discussions of the policy of each country with
                    regard to shared problems and the efforts by each to understand the other’s
                    policy, to achieve a common policy or to agree to differ.</p>
            </div>
